@NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder putUserProperty(@NotNull
                                                          @NotNull String key,
                                                          @NotNull
                                                          @NotNull String value)
        Associates the provided value with the provided key in this builder's user properties. If the builder previously contained an association for the key, the old value is replaced by the provided value.

        The key will be used as a Google Analytics "user property" key with the associated value.

        Parameters:
        key - to associate
        value - to associate with the key
        Returns:
        this builder

      • withFrequencyLimit

        @NotNull
@NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder withFrequencyLimit(int messages,
                                                             long duration,
                                                             @NotNull
                                                             @NotNull TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Limits the frequency by which events can be sent upstream to Google Analytics.

        Events that are posted within the provided time limit, counted from the time the last message was successfully attempted upstream, are silently dropped.

        Thus, the highest rate of messages sent upstream can be calculated using the following function <p> 1.0d/timeUnit.toSeconds(duration) <p> which yields messages per second.

        Parameters:
        messages - max number of messages to send per duration
        duration - minimum duration between upstream messages.
        timeUnit - for the provided duration.
        Returns:
        this builder

      • withErrorLogger

        @NotNull
@NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder withErrorLogger(@NotNull
                                                          @NotNull Consumer<? super String> errorLogger)
        Specifies a custom logger that will receive error messages. For example, failed HTTP communications.

        The default logger is System.err::println, i.e. messages will be output to the error console.

        The actual messages sent to the error logger are unspecified and shall not be acted on by logic.

        Parameters:
        errorLogger - to use for error messages.
        Returns:
        this builder

      • withDebugLogger

        @NotNull
@NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder withDebugLogger(@NotNull
                                                          @NotNull Consumer<? super String> debugLogger)
        Specifies a custom logger that will receive debug messages. For example, HTTP messages sent back and forth.

        The default logger is s -> {}, i.e. messages will be discarded.

        The actual messages sent to the debug logger are unspecified and shall not be acted on by logic.

        Parameters:
        debugLogger - to use for debug messages.
        Returns:
        this builder

      • withClientIdFileName

        @NotNull
@NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder withClientIdFileName(@NotNull
                                                               @NotNull String clientIdFileName)
        Specifies a custom file name to use when storing a persistent client id used to identify returning users.

        By default, a file named "chronicle.analytics.client.id" located in the user's home directory will be used.

        Parameters:
        clientIdFileName - used to store the persistent client id.
        Returns:
        this builder

      • withUrl

        @NotNull
@NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder withUrl(@NotNull
                                                  @NotNull String url)
        Specifies a custom URL to use when connecting to Google Analytics.

        By default, the URL "https://www.google-analytics.com/mp/collect" will be used.

        Parameters:
        url - used for remote connection
        Returns:
        this builder

      • withReportDespiteJUnit

        @NotNull
@NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder withReportDespiteJUnit()
        Specifies that reporting shall be made even though JUnit test classes are available to the classloader.

        By default, no reporting will be done if either of the classes `org.junit.jupiter.api.Test` or `org.junit.Test` are available to the classloader.

        Returns:
        this builder
